PLANTS OF CLEBURNE COUNTY, ALABAMA

*Galax urceolata* (J. Poiret) R. Brummitt
DIAPENSIACEAE

Talladega National Forest: 0.6 mi NE on forest road 651 from its jct. with the road to Cheaha State Park, SE of Anniston, W of the park. Mesic riparian creekside with sandy loam soil. Elevation ca. 410 m. Associates *Acer*, *Quercus*, *Rhododendron*, *Pinus*, *Liriodendron*, *Liquidambar*, *Toxicodendron*, *Vaccinium*, *Panicum*, *Danthonia*, *Alnus*, *Xanthorhiza*, *Itea*, and *Carex*.
Flowers white
Occasional
